title: The Chimneys Scuffle. [A satire, in verse. By Richard Brathwait?]

The Coffee Scuffle, occasioned by a contest between a learned Knight, and a pitifull pedagogue. With the character of a Coffee-House. [With a MS. note, “This is thought to be made by one Woolnoth on Evans a schoole mr & Sir James Langham.”]
The Jewes Tragedy, or, their fatal and final overthrow by Vespatian and Titus his son. Agreeable to the authentick and famous history of Josephus. [In five acts and in verse.]
first_author: HEMINGS, William M.A., of Christ Church, Oxford
